WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Our scripture passage this morning comes from Matthew 28 verse 16.

2
00:00:07.700 --> 00:00:12.800
Now the eleven disciples went to Galilee to the mountain to which Jesus had directed them.

3
00:00:12.800 --> 00:00:16.300
And when they saw him, they worshiped him. But some doubted.

4
00:00:16.300 --> 00:00:18.500
And Jesus came and said to them,

5
00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:22.100
All authority in heaven and on earth has been given to me.

6
00:00:22.100 --> 00:00:25.100
Go therefore and make disciples of all nations,

7
00:00:25.100 --> 00:00:29.700
baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit.

8
00:00:29.900 --> 00:00:32.800
Teaching them to observe all that I have commanded you.

9
00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:36.300
And behold, I am with you always to the end of the age.

10
00:00:36.300 --> 00:00:37.800
This is the word of the Lord.

11
00:00:41.600 --> 00:00:42.700
Thank you, Lauren.

12
00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:50.700
Well, about a mile and a half down the road from here at the foot of Lasseter Mountain

13
00:00:50.700 --> 00:00:52.300
is a pear tree.

14
00:00:52.300 --> 00:00:56.600
And when I was a little boy, I used to climb into that pear tree.

15
00:00:56.600 --> 00:00:59.700
It was there in our driveway in our family home.

16
00:00:59.700 --> 00:01:05.400
And I remember perching in my favorite spot on that pear tree and just letting my mind roam

17
00:01:05.400 --> 00:01:07.800
and my imagination go wild.

18
00:01:07.800 --> 00:01:12.900
And I remember just dreaming about what might be to come in the future.

19
00:01:12.900 --> 00:01:17.700
And, you know, I never became a spy.

20
00:01:17.700 --> 00:01:19.400
Like I thought I might be one day.

21
00:01:19.400 --> 00:01:24.500
I never even became an NBA basketball star, sadly.

22
00:01:24.500 --> 00:01:31.600
But I can honestly say that God did more than I could have ever have anticipated.

23
00:01:31.600 --> 00:01:39.200
And one thing I'm not sure I did anticipate was to be right back where I was then

24
00:01:39.200 --> 00:01:40.700
for it to come full circle.

25
00:01:40.700 --> 00:01:47.400
And it is really surreal to be back here not only in Alabama, but in North Jefferson County

26
00:01:47.400 --> 00:01:52.800
just down the road from Archer Road where that pear tree is.

27
00:01:52.800 --> 00:01:59.900
And this morning we're looking at the end of the Gospel of Matthew.

28
00:01:59.900 --> 00:02:05.800
And here in the book of Matthew, Jesus has come to the end of his earthly ministry.

29
00:02:05.800 --> 00:02:13.900
And here at the very end of his earthly ministry, he brings his disciples right back to where they started.

30
00:02:13.900 --> 00:02:16.800
Right back to where it all began.

31
00:02:16.800 --> 00:02:19.800
He took them to Galilee.

32
00:02:19.800 --> 00:02:24.300
And in many ways, this was a surprising place for Jesus to begin his ministry

33
00:02:24.300 --> 00:02:29.700
and perhaps a surprising place for him to give what is now known as the Great Commission.

34
00:02:29.700 --> 00:02:34.500
Because you see, the religious establishment was not from Galilee.

35
00:02:34.500 --> 00:02:37.900
They were further south in Judea.

36
00:02:37.900 --> 00:02:44.700
The Galileans were kind of their country cousins who lived further north.

37
00:02:44.700 --> 00:02:48.900
A lot of them were fishermen and farmers by trade.

38
00:02:48.900 --> 00:02:52.600
In fact, they were known for their country accents.

39
00:02:52.600 --> 00:02:59.800
So if you were down in Judea and you wanted to tell a joke, you might put on a thick Galilean accent.

40
00:02:59.800 --> 00:03:08.800
And also in Galilee, they were kind of country folk, but also their religion was practiced a little bit loosely, shall we say.

41
00:03:08.800 --> 00:03:18.300
They identified as being Jews, but they were heavily influenced by the culture that was around them.

42
00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:20.300
And they were known for that.

43
00:03:20.300 --> 00:03:27.900
I wonder if any of that sounds familiar in terms of the context of where we are sat here this morning.

44
00:03:27.900 --> 00:03:34.900
And yet, this is where Jesus chose to begin his earthly ministry.

45
00:03:34.900 --> 00:03:39.200
This is where he chose his disciples from.

46
00:03:39.200 --> 00:03:46.700
As far as we can tell, every single one of the 11 disciples gathered here were from Galilee.

47
00:03:46.700 --> 00:03:51.700
By the way, a side note, the only one who wasn't was a man called Judas Iscariot.

48
00:03:51.700 --> 00:03:55.300
And now the Galileans are all here together.

49
00:03:55.300 --> 00:03:58.600
So why does he bring them back to Galilee?

50
00:03:58.600 --> 00:04:04.200
Well, I have to say to the nostalgia I feel at the moment, it's not for nostalgia's sake.

51
00:04:04.200 --> 00:04:09.200
There was some significance to the place itself and their shared stories there,

52
00:04:09.200 --> 00:04:15.700
but more important is what these disciples witnessed there in Galilee.

53
00:04:15.700 --> 00:04:19.700
Because it was there that they first saw Jesus.

54
00:04:19.700 --> 00:04:24.200
It was there that they first heard the words, follow me.

55
00:04:24.200 --> 00:04:30.000
So now in these final moments, he takes them back to where they witnessed those things

56
00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:35.300
and they heard those words and he draws everything that they've seen over the past three years together

57
00:04:35.300 --> 00:04:42.100
into a final statement about who he truly is and what it truly means to follow him.

58
00:04:42.100 --> 00:04:46.000
So as we get started today, can I ask you a question?

59
00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:48.200
Why are you here?

60
00:04:48.200 --> 00:04:54.200
Not in Galilee, but in North Jefferson County in Mount Olive.

61
00:04:54.200 --> 00:04:58.400
What drew you to this church plant?

62
00:04:58.400 --> 00:05:00.400
I imagine there's probably lots of reasons.

63
00:05:00.400 --> 00:05:06.200
It could be the maybe the pioneering nature of the thing is a draw for some folks

64
00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:10.100
or maybe you've got friends or family who are here.

65
00:05:10.100 --> 00:05:14.800
Maybe you've experienced disappointments in a church you've been at.

66
00:05:14.800 --> 00:05:19.200
Maybe it's just closer to home where you actually live.

67
00:05:19.200 --> 00:05:23.400
Maybe you're not sure why you're here, but you're testing the waters to see what this is all about.

68
00:05:23.400 --> 00:05:28.600
Maybe, I don't know, you heard there's barbecue and you were hungry and you wanted to come here.

69
00:05:28.600 --> 00:05:32.900
It's probably honestly a mix of a few things for all of us.

70
00:05:32.900 --> 00:05:38.500
But whatever your reasons for coming, I want us to see that we are ultimately here for the very same reason

71
00:05:38.500 --> 00:05:43.600
that Jesus gathered his disciples on that day.

72
00:05:43.600 --> 00:05:49.800
So we're here for, let's say, four reasons from Matthew chapter 28.

73
00:05:49.800 --> 00:05:55.500
First of all, we are here because number one, Jesus has all authority.

74
00:05:55.500 --> 00:05:59.000
Everything in the passage and everything that would happen afterwards,

75
00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:02.800
including us being sat here right here in this moment,

76
00:06:02.800 --> 00:06:07.700
flows from what Jesus says in verse 18.

77
00:06:07.700 --> 00:06:15.000
When he says, all authority in heaven and on earth has been given to me.

78
00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:16.900
Afterwards, you'll see the little word therefore.

79
00:06:16.900 --> 00:06:23.400
So everything that's going to happen is connected to his authority.

80
00:06:23.400 --> 00:06:25.400
When Jesus comes to the disciples in the passage,

81
00:06:25.400 --> 00:06:28.500
you may have noticed that he was met with a mixed response.

82
00:06:28.500 --> 00:06:32.600
Some are worshiping him, but others of them are doubting.

83
00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:37.200
Now remember, he's just been brutally murdered and now here he is.

84
00:06:37.200 --> 00:06:38.200
He's risen from the dead.

85
00:06:38.200 --> 00:06:45.000
Some are elated and they're all in with worship and others just cannot believe their eyes.

86
00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:48.500
So it's hard to maybe interpret what it is that they are seeing in front of them.

87
00:06:48.500 --> 00:06:54.200
So Jesus does the interpreting for them and he makes it absolutely clear this is who they are looking at.

88
00:06:54.200 --> 00:06:56.900
He doesn't give them some parable now or cryptic statement.

89
00:06:56.900 --> 00:07:01.800
He plainly tells them exactly who he is.

90
00:07:01.800 --> 00:07:04.100
He's the one who possesses all authority.

91
00:07:04.100 --> 00:07:08.700
He's the King who reigns over all things.

92
00:07:08.700 --> 00:07:15.500
Now his kingly authority has been a theme that is stretched right the way throughout the gospel of Matthew.

93
00:07:15.500 --> 00:07:19.500
So if you go back to the very first verse, you know, you got a genealogy given there,

94
00:07:19.500 --> 00:07:25.200
but right from the beginning Jesus has introduced to us as the son of David.

95
00:07:25.200 --> 00:07:25.500
Right?

96
00:07:25.500 --> 00:07:27.400
So we see the connection with King David.

97
00:07:27.400 --> 00:07:33.400
He was the promised offspring of King David who was to be given a kingdom that would last forever.

98
00:07:33.400 --> 00:07:36.700
When the wise men came seeking Jesus, who did they come seeking?

99
00:07:36.700 --> 00:07:41.800
They came seeking the one who is to be King.

100
00:07:41.800 --> 00:07:45.400
When he preaches his first sermon, what is his message?

101
00:07:45.400 --> 00:07:52.200
Repent for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.

102
00:07:52.200 --> 00:07:56.000
His authority is then seen as he goes about his ministry.

103
00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:58.200
His authority is seen as his teaching.

104
00:07:58.200 --> 00:08:03.700
You hear him saying things like, you have heard it said, but I say unto you.

105
00:08:03.700 --> 00:08:09.200
When he speaks, it's obvious that the truth that he is speaking isn't derivative of somewhere else.

106
00:08:09.200 --> 00:08:14.200
He is the very source of truth itself in what he says.

107
00:08:14.200 --> 00:08:20.800
And so when people hear him, they say he's speaking as someone who is speaking with authority,

108
00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:23.200
not as our scribes.

109
00:08:23.200 --> 00:08:26.700
His authority is also seen in his miracles.

110
00:08:26.700 --> 00:08:29.000
He has power over the elements.

111
00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:30.300
He calms the storms.

112
00:08:30.300 --> 00:08:33.100
He has power to heal diseases.

113
00:08:33.100 --> 00:08:35.500
He has power to cast out demons.

114
00:08:35.500 --> 00:08:37.900
He has power to raise the dead.

115
00:08:37.900 --> 00:08:43.800
Life itself was in his hands.

116
00:08:43.800 --> 00:08:48.500
He even has the power to forgive sins.

117
00:08:48.500 --> 00:08:52.900
The religious authorities of his day thought he was being blasphemous.

118
00:08:52.900 --> 00:08:56.500
And they said, who can forgive sins but God alone?

119
00:08:56.500 --> 00:09:00.100
How can he claim this for himself?

120
00:09:00.100 --> 00:09:03.200
And so they opposed his authority.

121
00:09:03.200 --> 00:09:07.700
And that opposition to his authority eventually led to his death.

122
00:09:07.700 --> 00:09:14.900
And in his death, it's interesting that the thing that they mock is his kingly authority.

123
00:09:14.900 --> 00:09:17.000
So what do they do?

124
00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:23.000
When he's brought before the authorities, they put a robe on him.

125
00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:28.000
And they put a crown on him, a crown of thorns on him.

126
00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:30.200
They give him a reed as though it was a scepter.

127
00:09:30.200 --> 00:09:36.000
And they kneel before him and they mockingly say, Hail, King of the Jews.

128
00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:38.800
And they spit on him.

129
00:09:38.800 --> 00:09:40.800
And they strike him with a scepter.

130
00:09:40.800 --> 00:09:45.500
And they rip the robe from off his back.

131
00:09:45.500 --> 00:09:49.700
He's then lifted up, but not on a throne, but on a cross.

132
00:09:49.700 --> 00:09:52.300
And over the cross reads, What?

133
00:09:52.300 --> 00:09:57.000
This is Jesus, King of the Jews.

134
00:09:57.000 --> 00:10:00.000
And as he's up there, they hurl insults at him saying,

135
00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:01.000
He saved others.

136
00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:04.300
He cannot save himself.

137
00:10:04.300 --> 00:10:08.000
Of course, he was able to save himself, but he chose not to.

138
00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:09.800
Why?

139
00:10:09.800 --> 00:10:12.700
Because he was there to save us.

140
00:10:12.700 --> 00:10:21.800
He was there dying in the place of rebels, people who rebel against his authority so that we might be reconciled to God.

141
00:10:21.800 --> 00:10:24.500
He was there dying in the place of sinners.

142
00:10:24.500 --> 00:10:30.100
He was there in his authority accomplishing what he came to do.

143
00:10:30.100 --> 00:10:35.500
Then his authority is finally seen when he rises from the dead.

144
00:10:35.500 --> 00:10:38.100
He conquers the grave.

145
00:10:38.100 --> 00:10:39.500
He rises in power.

146
00:10:39.500 --> 00:10:41.800
The King has defeated sin.

147
00:10:41.800 --> 00:10:46.300
He has defeated the powers of evil and he's defeated death itself.

148
00:10:46.300 --> 00:10:51.000
And so now before his disciples, before us in his word,

149
00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:53.200
he makes it clear this is who he is.

150
00:10:53.200 --> 00:10:56.700
This is the extent of his authority.

151
00:10:56.700 --> 00:11:00.600
All of it belongs to him, all authority in heaven and on earth.

152
00:11:00.600 --> 00:11:04.000
Abraham Kuiper had it right when he said,

153
00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:13.100
There is not a square inch in the whole domain of our human existence over which Christ, who is sovereign over all, does not cry mine.

154
00:11:13.100 --> 00:11:21.000
His dominion extends over every place, every person and every part of our existence.

155
00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:24.200
So how should we respond to him?

156
00:11:24.200 --> 00:11:29.900
If he is over it all, we should open up the whole of our lives to him.

157
00:11:29.900 --> 00:11:33.200
So that brings us to the second reason why we're here.

158
00:11:33.200 --> 00:11:39.800
Or at least why we ought to be is because number two, Jesus calls us to follow him.

159
00:11:39.800 --> 00:11:41.000
He calls us to follow him.

160
00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:47.000
This great revelation of who Jesus is is followed by what is often called the Great Commission,

161
00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:51.200
where he tells his disciples to go and make disciples of all nations.

162
00:11:51.200 --> 00:11:53.000
We're going to get to that in a moment.

163
00:11:53.000 --> 00:11:57.400
But before we see that we're called to participate in making disciples,

164
00:11:57.400 --> 00:12:01.300
we are first recipients of those who responded to that call.

165
00:12:01.300 --> 00:12:06.000
In other words, we're called to be disciples of Jesus.

166
00:12:06.000 --> 00:12:07.800
So what does this actually mean?

167
00:12:07.800 --> 00:12:11.200
Right? As these disciples are going out to then make other disciples,

168
00:12:11.200 --> 00:12:16.200
and the message has come to us here today, well, what does it mean to then be a disciple of Jesus?

169
00:12:16.200 --> 00:12:21.300
Does it mean, I don't know, every head bowed, every eye closed, no one looking around?

170
00:12:21.300 --> 00:12:23.900
Does it mean like walk the aisle at the end of the service?

171
00:12:23.900 --> 00:12:26.200
Does it mean repeat a prayer after someone?

172
00:12:26.200 --> 00:12:31.000
Does it mean commit to only exclusively listen to Christian radio from here on out?

173
00:12:31.000 --> 00:12:36.700
Like what does it mean to be a disciple of Jesus?

174
00:12:36.700 --> 00:12:38.800
Well, a couple of things. We can say lots of things,

175
00:12:38.800 --> 00:12:44.000
but a couple of things just grounded in what we see in the text itself here today.

176
00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:48.500
One thing is it means receiving a new identity.

177
00:12:48.500 --> 00:12:52.600
When you become a follower of Jesus, your life no longer belongs to yourself.

178
00:12:52.600 --> 00:12:54.800
It belongs to him.

179
00:12:54.800 --> 00:12:58.200
Right? He's in charge, not me.

180
00:12:58.200 --> 00:13:05.200
It means letting go of our resistance to Jesus and instead receiving him as our King.

181
00:13:05.300 --> 00:13:09.400
When you repent of your sin and you put your faith in Jesus,

182
00:13:09.400 --> 00:13:13.300
you are united to him in his death and resurrection.

183
00:13:13.300 --> 00:13:17.100
Your old life is gone and you've been given a new life in him.

184
00:13:17.100 --> 00:13:21.000
You are now a follower of his. You belong to him.

185
00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:23.900
Your life is bound with his.

186
00:13:23.900 --> 00:13:28.700
And that union with Jesus is represented in baptism.

187
00:13:28.700 --> 00:13:30.500
Right? So he tells his disciples here,

188
00:13:30.500 --> 00:13:32.600
go make disciples of all nations,

189
00:13:32.600 --> 00:13:39.000
baptizing them in the name of the Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.

190
00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:40.700
More about that in a second.

191
00:13:40.700 --> 00:13:46.100
But just as a little caveat here, you might think it's oppressive to think like,

192
00:13:46.100 --> 00:13:50.000
oh, I belong to someone. I belong to Jesus.

193
00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:57.100
But remember, to belong to Jesus is more liberating than anything you will ever experience.

194
00:13:57.100 --> 00:14:03.800
To belong to him is to be set free from sin and from the forces of evil

195
00:14:03.800 --> 00:14:08.400
and to be empowered to live the life that you were made for.

196
00:14:08.400 --> 00:14:16.800
To belong to Jesus isn't so much binding as it is liberating

197
00:14:16.800 --> 00:14:22.100
because you belong to someone who cares for you far more than you could ever care for yourself.

198
00:14:22.100 --> 00:14:27.200
One of the ways that belonging is communicated is through a family name.

199
00:14:27.200 --> 00:14:30.300
I don't know if you've noticed, but over the years,

200
00:14:30.300 --> 00:14:33.000
names seem to become a bit more individualized.

201
00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:34.700
Has anybody else noticed that?

202
00:14:34.700 --> 00:14:37.500
Maybe the older you are in here, the more you can see.

203
00:14:37.500 --> 00:14:41.300
Years ago, decades ago, there was just a handful of names,

204
00:14:41.300 --> 00:14:43.900
just kind of standard names that are given out.

205
00:14:43.900 --> 00:14:47.000
And whereas now, I don't want to give examples

206
00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:49.200
as to name somebody who sat here,

207
00:14:49.200 --> 00:14:51.200
but everybody's given a very specific name.

208
00:14:51.200 --> 00:14:53.300
And if you're given a traditional name,

209
00:14:53.300 --> 00:14:56.500
it's got to have unique spelling that goes along with it.

210
00:14:56.500 --> 00:14:58.800
So I feel sorry for those who are teachers.

211
00:14:58.800 --> 00:15:01.500
I have to spell all these kids' names and remember all the names.

212
00:15:01.500 --> 00:15:04.500
And by the way, I checked out the statistics last week

213
00:15:04.500 --> 00:15:05.700
and I was like, is this just me?

214
00:15:05.700 --> 00:15:08.400
No, actually, that has increased in recent generations

215
00:15:08.400 --> 00:15:09.900
and there's probably reasons for that.

216
00:15:09.900 --> 00:15:12.500
We won't get into it now.

217
00:15:12.500 --> 00:15:14.300
But as those names have changed,

218
00:15:14.300 --> 00:15:16.600
there's something else that hasn't changed much,

219
00:15:16.600 --> 00:15:19.000
at least nowhere near at the same rate.

220
00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:21.700
And that is people's last names,

221
00:15:21.700 --> 00:15:28.100
the family names that they were born into.

222
00:15:28.100 --> 00:15:31.400
In Numbers 6 and verse 27,

223
00:15:31.400 --> 00:15:34.300
God has looked on His people and He says,

224
00:15:34.300 --> 00:15:38.000
They are mine, they belong to me,

225
00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:40.900
and I'm going to put my name on them.

226
00:15:40.900 --> 00:15:43.800
Right? So they're His family.

227
00:15:43.800 --> 00:15:47.600
And one of the ways that this would be communicated to His people

228
00:15:47.600 --> 00:15:52.100
was by a blessing that would be spoken over them by Aaron.

229
00:15:52.100 --> 00:15:55.000
His singular name,

230
00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:56.100
the name that had been put on them

231
00:15:56.100 --> 00:15:59.500
was going to be spoken over them three times.

232
00:15:59.500 --> 00:16:00.900
I wonder if you know the verse.

233
00:16:00.900 --> 00:16:02.300
Here's the blessing.

234
00:16:02.300 --> 00:16:05.700
The Lord bless you and keep you.

235
00:16:05.700 --> 00:16:07.700
The Lord, there's the name again,

236
00:16:07.700 --> 00:16:10.300
make His face to shine upon you

237
00:16:10.300 --> 00:16:12.300
and be gracious to you.

238
00:16:12.300 --> 00:16:16.200
The Lord lift up His countenance upon you

239
00:16:16.200 --> 00:16:17.800
and give you peace.

240
00:16:17.800 --> 00:16:22.900
The Lord, the Lord, the Lord.

241
00:16:22.900 --> 00:16:26.200
Today, through faith in Jesus,

242
00:16:26.200 --> 00:16:28.500
we are brought into the family of God,

243
00:16:28.500 --> 00:16:32.700
into the loving relationship of the Father, Son, and Spirit.

244
00:16:32.700 --> 00:16:35.100
You might say we are brought into,

245
00:16:35.100 --> 00:16:39.600
I've got to say it, Trinity Fellowship.

246
00:16:39.600 --> 00:16:41.800
And when we're brought into that relationship with God

247
00:16:41.800 --> 00:16:43.900
through faith in Jesus,

248
00:16:43.900 --> 00:16:45.100
He puts His name on us.

249
00:16:45.100 --> 00:16:48.900
He speaks His name over us.

250
00:16:48.900 --> 00:16:51.200
And where is God's name spoken over His people today?

251
00:16:51.200 --> 00:16:55.000
Where do we hear that communicated?

252
00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:56.400
Well, here we see it,

253
00:16:56.400 --> 00:17:01.200
baptizing them in the singular name of the Father

254
00:17:01.200 --> 00:17:05.400
and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit.

255
00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:08.000
So baptism shows us that we are identified,

256
00:17:08.000 --> 00:17:10.300
we have identified with the Lord in His death

257
00:17:10.300 --> 00:17:11.400
and in His resurrection,

258
00:17:11.400 --> 00:17:13.000
but it's also a naming ceremony,

259
00:17:13.000 --> 00:17:14.400
like the threefold blessing,

260
00:17:14.400 --> 00:17:16.600
spoken by Aaron over God's people.

261
00:17:16.600 --> 00:17:21.300
We're baptized in the name of the Father, Son, and Spirit.

262
00:17:21.300 --> 00:17:23.900
But what's happening there?

263
00:17:23.900 --> 00:17:25.300
When we're trusting in Christ,

264
00:17:25.300 --> 00:17:26.700
when we are united to Him,

265
00:17:26.700 --> 00:17:28.100
God is saying,

266
00:17:28.100 --> 00:17:30.500
you belong to me, your mind.

267
00:17:30.500 --> 00:17:34.500
We've been given a new identity as a follower of Jesus.

268
00:17:34.500 --> 00:17:38.600
Secondly, we're given a new way of life.

269
00:17:38.600 --> 00:17:40.700
It's about a new way of life.

270
00:17:40.700 --> 00:17:42.300
The reality of the new life

271
00:17:42.300 --> 00:17:44.400
that we're given through Jesus

272
00:17:44.400 --> 00:17:50.200
is lived out as we walk in step with Jesus.

273
00:17:50.200 --> 00:17:53.500
You see here that disciples are told to do what?

274
00:17:53.500 --> 00:17:58.400
To observe all that He has commanded them.

275
00:17:58.400 --> 00:18:00.200
And by the way, notice it doesn't say,

276
00:18:00.200 --> 00:18:03.600
teaching them all that I have commanded you.

277
00:18:03.600 --> 00:18:04.500
I don't know about you,

278
00:18:04.500 --> 00:18:08.600
but I've heard this passage before taught in this way.

279
00:18:08.600 --> 00:18:09.200
But it doesn't say,

280
00:18:09.200 --> 00:18:11.500
teach them all that I've commanded you.

281
00:18:11.600 --> 00:18:14.200
It says, teach them to what?

282
00:18:14.200 --> 00:18:17.800
To observe all that I have commanded you.

283
00:18:17.800 --> 00:18:20.200
Well, of course, you've got to be taught it to observe it.

284
00:18:20.200 --> 00:18:21.900
But the thing that's being taught here

285
00:18:21.900 --> 00:18:23.700
is that way of life, the practice,

286
00:18:23.700 --> 00:18:27.100
this obedience that we are being called to.

287
00:18:27.100 --> 00:18:28.700
So, disciples are not those

288
00:18:28.700 --> 00:18:31.400
who merely know the way of Jesus.

289
00:18:31.400 --> 00:18:35.200
Disciples are those who follow the way of Jesus.

290
00:18:35.200 --> 00:18:37.300
The way we can see that we belong to Him,

291
00:18:37.300 --> 00:18:40.000
that we really have been united to Christ by faith,

292
00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:45.900
is in our walk with Him.

293
00:18:45.900 --> 00:18:48.100
So, let's not make the mistake of equating

294
00:18:48.100 --> 00:18:50.900
the quantity of knowledge we have

295
00:18:50.900 --> 00:18:54.500
with the quality of our discipleship.

296
00:18:54.500 --> 00:18:56.400
And I think particularly in the Western world,

297
00:18:56.400 --> 00:18:59.300
in like North America, in places in Europe,

298
00:18:59.300 --> 00:19:00.900
we're quick to do that.

299
00:19:00.900 --> 00:19:04.600
I think discipleship equals the amount that I know

300
00:19:04.600 --> 00:19:09.800
rather than the life that has been changed.

301
00:19:09.800 --> 00:19:11.900
In the early 20th century,

302
00:19:11.900 --> 00:19:13.900
there was a Swiss theologian

303
00:19:13.900 --> 00:19:15.500
who was considered by many to be

304
00:19:15.500 --> 00:19:17.500
the greatest Christian intellectual

305
00:19:17.500 --> 00:19:21.000
of the 20th century.

306
00:19:21.000 --> 00:19:25.300
He was published over 600 times his works.

307
00:19:25.300 --> 00:19:30.100
His longest work was over 9,000 pages long,

308
00:19:30.100 --> 00:19:33.300
stretching across 13 volumes.

309
00:19:33.300 --> 00:19:35.400
But one of his last works to be published

310
00:19:35.400 --> 00:19:37.300
long after he died

311
00:19:37.300 --> 00:19:39.800
was his decades-long correspondence

312
00:19:39.800 --> 00:19:46.300
with his mistress.

313
00:19:46.300 --> 00:19:49.100
But on the flip side,

314
00:19:49.100 --> 00:19:54.300
you know, there's often a village in Senegal.

315
00:19:54.300 --> 00:19:56.800
There's a grandmother who's there.

316
00:19:56.800 --> 00:19:58.400
She's never learned to read.

317
00:19:58.400 --> 00:20:04.000
She's never had the opportunity to learn how to read.

318
00:20:04.000 --> 00:20:06.200
But she knows Jesus.

319
00:20:06.200 --> 00:20:07.200
She loves him.

320
00:20:07.200 --> 00:20:10.000
And she's eager to gather with the people of God

321
00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:11.200
every single week.

322
00:20:11.200 --> 00:20:12.400
And she goes hungry.

323
00:20:12.400 --> 00:20:14.500
And she listens to the Word of God.

324
00:20:14.500 --> 00:20:18.000
And she is being transformed into the likeness of Jesus.

325
00:20:18.000 --> 00:20:19.700
She's growing in love for him

326
00:20:19.700 --> 00:20:24.000
and growing in love for her neighbor.

327
00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:25.800
Let me ask you,

328
00:20:25.800 --> 00:20:30.400
which one is following Jesus?

329
00:20:30.400 --> 00:20:34.100
The one who knows just about everything there is to know

330
00:20:34.100 --> 00:20:39.300
or the one who is following what he's given them.

331
00:20:39.300 --> 00:20:40.300
Don't mishear me.

332
00:20:40.300 --> 00:20:44.300
I hope we swim in some deep theological waters

333
00:20:44.300 --> 00:20:46.600
here at Trinity Fellowship.

334
00:20:46.600 --> 00:20:47.600
For sure.

335
00:20:47.600 --> 00:20:49.100
I mean, our first series is starting next week.

336
00:20:49.100 --> 00:20:50.100
It's on the Book of Ephesians.

337
00:20:50.100 --> 00:20:52.300
So get ready.

338
00:20:52.300 --> 00:20:55.100
But let's pray that the depths of our theology

339
00:20:55.100 --> 00:21:01.300
is matched by the depths of our discipleship.

340
00:21:01.300 --> 00:21:03.600
Now, this doesn't mean we're going to follow Jesus perfectly.

341
00:21:03.600 --> 00:21:09.100
We will fail time and time again.

342
00:21:09.100 --> 00:21:12.600
By the way, if it's any encouragement,

343
00:21:12.600 --> 00:21:15.600
his original crew didn't follow him perfectly either.

344
00:21:15.600 --> 00:21:16.600
Remember what they're doing here.

345
00:21:16.600 --> 00:21:19.600
Some of them are worshiping and others are doubting.

346
00:21:19.600 --> 00:21:20.600
Right?

347
00:21:20.600 --> 00:21:22.600
They're there with their doubts, their fears.

348
00:21:22.600 --> 00:21:25.100
This word for doubt is only used one other time in Matthew.

349
00:21:25.100 --> 00:21:26.600
And it's when Peter sank.

350
00:21:26.600 --> 00:21:29.600
Do you remember he was walking on the water with Jesus?

351
00:21:29.600 --> 00:21:32.600
And then he starts to look at the wind and the waves around him

352
00:21:32.600 --> 00:21:33.600
and he begins to sink.

353
00:21:33.600 --> 00:21:36.600
He says, Jesus saved me and Jesus draws him out of the water

354
00:21:36.600 --> 00:21:41.100
and he says, oh, you of little faith, why did you doubt?

355
00:21:41.100 --> 00:21:43.100
So there was a mingling there of like Peter had the faith

356
00:21:43.100 --> 00:21:44.600
to step out onto the water.

357
00:21:44.600 --> 00:21:46.100
He's looking to Jesus.

358
00:21:46.100 --> 00:21:48.600
He's been saved by Jesus.

359
00:21:48.600 --> 00:21:50.600
But there's still room to grow.

360
00:21:50.600 --> 00:21:55.100
And that's the case for all of us here.

361
00:21:55.100 --> 00:22:00.600
As we follow Jesus, we will do so with imperfect faith.

362
00:22:00.600 --> 00:22:02.600
But we can do so knowing that he will be with us

363
00:22:02.600 --> 00:22:05.100
and will draw us back to himself time and time again.

364
00:22:05.100 --> 00:22:09.600
Our imperfect faith is in a perfect Savior.

365
00:22:09.600 --> 00:22:11.100
Third reason why we're here.

366
00:22:11.100 --> 00:22:16.600
We're here because Jesus sends us to make disciples.

367
00:22:16.600 --> 00:22:20.600
So the central imperative or command in verses 18 and 19

368
00:22:20.600 --> 00:22:23.100
is make disciples.

369
00:22:23.100 --> 00:22:25.100
In the other words around it show how that's done

370
00:22:25.100 --> 00:22:27.600
by going, baptizing and teaching.

371
00:22:27.600 --> 00:22:29.600
And Jesus here, you can see,

372
00:22:29.600 --> 00:22:33.100
he doesn't give like a detailed list of instructions.

373
00:22:33.100 --> 00:22:36.100
One of the reasons that they are putting,

374
00:22:36.100 --> 00:22:38.100
he doesn't give a list of detailed instructions

375
00:22:38.100 --> 00:22:39.600
is that they're gonna put into practice

376
00:22:39.600 --> 00:22:41.600
what they've already seen in practice

377
00:22:41.600 --> 00:22:45.100
over the past three years with him.

378
00:22:45.100 --> 00:22:47.600
They are now to do what they have seen,

379
00:22:47.600 --> 00:22:49.600
they have received, and now they are to give

380
00:22:49.600 --> 00:22:52.600
out of what they have received.

381
00:22:52.600 --> 00:22:54.100
So they're to make disciples

382
00:22:54.100 --> 00:22:57.100
as they have been made disciples.

383
00:22:57.600 --> 00:23:00.600
So you might wonder, does this apply to us?

384
00:23:00.600 --> 00:23:02.600
Or is this just for the 11?

385
00:23:02.600 --> 00:23:05.600
Well if they are to teach the disciples to observe

386
00:23:05.600 --> 00:23:08.600
everything that they have been commanded,

387
00:23:08.600 --> 00:23:11.600
well what was the final command?

388
00:23:11.600 --> 00:23:14.600
Go make disciples, all right?

389
00:23:14.600 --> 00:23:17.600
So those who are made disciples are then called

390
00:23:17.600 --> 00:23:20.100
to go and make disciples of others.

391
00:23:20.100 --> 00:23:22.600
And that baton has been passed through the generations

392
00:23:22.600 --> 00:23:25.100
and has now come to us.

393
00:23:25.100 --> 00:23:26.600
Another way of saying this is to say

394
00:23:26.600 --> 00:23:29.600
that Trinity Fellowship does not exist

395
00:23:29.600 --> 00:23:32.600
merely for itself.

396
00:23:32.600 --> 00:23:35.100
Not to be gross, but ingrown things

397
00:23:35.100 --> 00:23:37.100
can be pretty nasty.

398
00:23:37.100 --> 00:23:40.100
And they can be hurtful.

399
00:23:40.100 --> 00:23:42.100
Let's not be an ingrown church.

400
00:23:42.100 --> 00:23:45.100
We exist not just for ourselves,

401
00:23:45.100 --> 00:23:48.100
but to go and to make disciples locally

402
00:23:48.100 --> 00:23:50.100
and globally to make Christ known

403
00:23:50.100 --> 00:23:54.100
to others in word or in deed.

404
00:23:54.100 --> 00:23:56.600
So disciples are called to be disciple makers

405
00:23:56.600 --> 00:23:58.100
and that includes us.

406
00:23:58.100 --> 00:23:59.100
And you know what?

407
00:23:59.100 --> 00:24:01.100
Church planting is a wonderful opportunity

408
00:24:01.100 --> 00:24:03.600
for a fostering disciple making.

409
00:24:03.600 --> 00:24:05.600
I love established churches

410
00:24:05.600 --> 00:24:08.600
and I hope one day we will be an established church.

411
00:24:08.600 --> 00:24:10.100
But you know at an established church

412
00:24:10.100 --> 00:24:12.100
it can be easy to slip into the habit

413
00:24:12.100 --> 00:24:15.100
of just turning up and receiving

414
00:24:15.100 --> 00:24:17.100
in a way that's different to planting.

415
00:24:17.100 --> 00:24:20.100
At a church plant, you know, it's all hands on deck.

416
00:24:20.100 --> 00:24:22.100
I mean you brought your own chair this morning,

417
00:24:22.100 --> 00:24:23.600
a lot of you so well done.

418
00:24:23.600 --> 00:24:25.600
Maybe you're here and you've gotten used to

419
00:24:25.600 --> 00:24:28.100
dropping off your kids at kids ministry every week.

420
00:24:28.100 --> 00:24:30.100
But now perhaps you're going to experience

421
00:24:30.100 --> 00:24:35.100
what it is like to serve in children's ministry as well.

422
00:24:37.100 --> 00:24:39.100
Maybe you've been involved in home groups before

423
00:24:39.100 --> 00:24:41.100
and it's been wonderful to attend a home group

424
00:24:41.100 --> 00:24:43.100
in the past and pretty soon you might very well

425
00:24:43.100 --> 00:24:46.100
be leading a home group.

426
00:24:46.100 --> 00:24:47.600
You know the list could go on.

427
00:24:47.600 --> 00:24:51.100
There's opportunities for disciple making.

428
00:24:51.600 --> 00:24:54.600
I also want to say this that those activities

429
00:24:54.600 --> 00:24:57.100
aren't necessarily the same as disciple making.

430
00:24:57.100 --> 00:24:59.100
They can be an essential part

431
00:24:59.100 --> 00:25:01.100
but let's not miss the point.

432
00:25:01.100 --> 00:25:03.600
Activity and business isn't the same as being there

433
00:25:03.600 --> 00:25:08.100
to see disciples made of Jesus.

434
00:25:08.100 --> 00:25:10.100
And so the command to go here implies

435
00:25:10.100 --> 00:25:11.600
that we're not going to sit around here

436
00:25:11.600 --> 00:25:14.100
waiting for people to come to us.

437
00:25:14.100 --> 00:25:15.600
The trajectory is outward.

438
00:25:15.600 --> 00:25:17.600
We're called to go to others.

439
00:25:17.600 --> 00:25:19.600
Where they are.

440
00:25:20.600 --> 00:25:22.600
And also the command to baptize

441
00:25:22.600 --> 00:25:24.600
means that we are going to be engaging with people

442
00:25:24.600 --> 00:25:28.600
who previously did not know the Lord.

443
00:25:28.600 --> 00:25:30.600
And then as we've seen here

444
00:25:30.600 --> 00:25:34.600
we're going to help them God willing to grow as disciples.

445
00:25:34.600 --> 00:25:36.600
Can I just say that one of the fears that I have

446
00:25:36.600 --> 00:25:39.600
about planting in Alabama in Jefferson County

447
00:25:39.600 --> 00:25:41.600
is that we're going to be a church

448
00:25:41.600 --> 00:25:45.600
that just shuffles the deck one more time.

449
00:25:45.600 --> 00:25:47.600
In other words like getting just a few more Christians

450
00:25:47.600 --> 00:25:51.100
from other churches and we're just going to swap around

451
00:25:51.100 --> 00:25:53.600
and actually miss the opportunity

452
00:25:53.600 --> 00:25:57.600
to find those who do not yet know Jesus

453
00:25:57.600 --> 00:26:01.600
and make him known to them.

454
00:26:01.600 --> 00:26:04.600
You know I'm very much open to welcoming folks

455
00:26:04.600 --> 00:26:05.600
from other churches.

456
00:26:05.600 --> 00:26:06.600
Don't get me wrong.

457
00:26:06.600 --> 00:26:09.600
And I especially if someone's in a place

458
00:26:09.600 --> 00:26:13.600
where they're not hearing all that Jesus commanded them

459
00:26:13.600 --> 00:26:15.600
for sure but let's not forget the Son of Man

460
00:26:15.600 --> 00:26:18.600
came to seek and to save the lost.

461
00:26:18.600 --> 00:26:24.600
He left the 90 and 9 and went after the one that was lost.

462
00:26:24.600 --> 00:26:29.600
That applies not only here but also around the world.

463
00:26:29.600 --> 00:26:31.600
From day one let's determine that we will be a church

464
00:26:31.600 --> 00:26:34.600
that is passionate about God's global mission.

465
00:26:34.600 --> 00:26:36.600
You know the gospel, praise God,

466
00:26:36.600 --> 00:26:38.600
has made its way around the world

467
00:26:38.600 --> 00:26:40.600
since this command was originally given.

468
00:26:40.600 --> 00:26:44.600
But here's where things are at up to like today.

469
00:26:44.600 --> 00:26:48.600
2024 today there are over 3 billion people

470
00:26:48.600 --> 00:26:52.600
who are living in either a people group or a place

471
00:26:52.600 --> 00:26:56.600
where there's little to no access to the gospel.

472
00:26:56.600 --> 00:26:58.600
In other words they're not just surrounded by people

473
00:26:58.600 --> 00:26:59.600
who have never heard.

474
00:26:59.600 --> 00:27:01.600
They're in a people group or a place that has never heard

475
00:27:01.600 --> 00:27:03.600
and there's no church that is there

476
00:27:03.600 --> 00:27:07.600
seeking to make Christ known to them.

477
00:27:07.600 --> 00:27:10.600
That's why we're here to make Christ known

478
00:27:10.600 --> 00:27:14.600
from North Jefferson to the ends of the earth.

479
00:27:14.600 --> 00:27:18.600
For some it may be going to one of those places

480
00:27:18.600 --> 00:27:22.600
and for others it may be sending and supporting those who go.

481
00:27:22.600 --> 00:27:25.600
But I pray that we would be a church that would participate

482
00:27:25.600 --> 00:27:29.600
